parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause intermittent stalling, which can lead to accidents, especially if the vehicle stalls while in motion or in a hazardous location.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls intermittently
often without warning
and may or may not restart immediately.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear brakes locking up can cause loss of control, skidding, or accidents, especially on wet or slippery roads.
symptoms: The rear brakes lock up
causing the vehicle to skid or lose control
often without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the MAP sensor can cause the engine to stall intermittently, which can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls intermittently
the vehicle hesitates or stumbles when accelerating
the engine check light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle experiences poor fuel economy
the vehicle has difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden lock-up of the steering rack and pinion can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult to maneuver the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or collisions.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn or locks up
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering feels stiff or tight
the steering rack and pinion make abnormal noises
the vehicle is difficult to steer
especially during morning start-up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission multi-function lever can cause intermittent stalling, which can lead to accidents, especially when the vehicle stalls in heavy traffic or on a slope, and can also cause inconvenience and frustration to the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls intermittently
the transmission shifts erratically
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of power
the transmission warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause the doors to malfunction, leading to difficulties in entering or exiting the vehicle, and potentially compromising safety and security.
symptoms: The doors will not lock or unlock
the doors lock or unlock unexpectedly
the door lock buttons do not respond
the doors are difficult to open or close
the door locks make a grinding or clicking noise.
